      • getSkeletonResourcePath

        public java.lang.String getSkeletonResourcePath()
        Description copied from class: ResourcePoint
        Skeleton resource path is a resource path with placeholders that you can replace with actual values during runtime. The path should be relative to the API base URL. For example: /user/{{ userId }} The default ResourcePoint.getResourcePath() method is expecting placeholders in the following format: {{ placeholderIdentifier }} ResourcePoint.getResourcePath() will replace the placeholders with the provided parameters.
        Specified by:
        getSkeletonResourcePath in class ResourcePoint<T>
        Returns:
        Returns a skeleton resource path.
